  "body": "When animating the max-height property in Safari, entering the leave state would trigger an animation to `max-height: 0` (I guess Safari interprets `auto` as `0` when transitioning on that property?). Then when the active state kicked in, it would jump and didn't really look right. Moving the `transition` css property to the active class fixed the issue for me and worked on Safari, Chrome and Firefox. Unfortunately I'm not in a position to test in IE at the moment, but I'll do that at my first convenience tomorrow.\n",
